{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W2ZctToSkyuFb26WKbQtJ7","type":"tool_result","content":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/App.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/utils/mock-simulation.ts\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/utils/profile-event-bus.ts\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/components/ProfilePage.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/components/ProfileLoot.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/components/ProfileSettings.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/components/AvatarSelectorModal.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/quests/context/QuestsContext.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/quests/utils/mock-simulation.ts\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/quests/types.ts\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/quests/components/TreasureChestPanel.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/quests/components/ChestDropNotification.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/quests/components/QuestsPanel.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/odds.ts\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/boss-raid/utils/mock-simulation.ts\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/boss-raid/utils/raid-event-bus.ts\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/crypto-crash/context/CryptoCrashContext.tsx\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/crypto-crash/utils/mock-simulation.ts\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/crypto-crash/types.ts\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/utils/mock-simulation.ts","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VpNLGkQCRfw2LavP3xMSER","session_id":"9011bcd3-c1e3-4ba2-996b-dc56e2b15fd6","uuid":"628ee516-d3d1-4815-93f8-2e8de3ebc297"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B6cMRAptCTDXLCz1L4M2Fe","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the E2E infrastructure files. Let me provide you with a comprehensive overview.\n\n---\n\n## E2E Local Test Infrastructure Summary\n\n### 1. **Fixtures** (`fixtures.ts`)\n\n**Available fixtures:**\n- `playerAPage` / `playerBPage` — isolated Playwright `Page` instances in separate browser contexts\n- `playerAContext` / `playerBContext` — isolated `BrowserContext` instances\n- `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair` — deterministic keypairs (read-only)\n- `connection` — shared `Connection` to the local RPC (confirmed commitment)\n\n**How it works:**\n- Creates isolated browser contexts via `createPlayerContext()` which injects `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` before page loads\n- The seed is the raw 32-byte array from each player's keypair\n- `TestWalletProvider` reads this seed at React render time to construct the correct `Keypair`\n- Each context has its own storage/session — zero cross-contamination\n\n**Usage pattern:**\n```typescript\ntest(\"name\", async ({ playerAPage, playerBPage, connection }) => { ... })\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Page-Object Helpers** (`page-objects.ts`)\n\n**Selectors:**\n```typescript\nsel = {\n  // Lobby structure\n  lobby: \".coinflip-lobby\",\n  sidebar: \".coinflip-sidebar\",\n  main: \".coinflip-main\",\n  \n  // Create flow\n  tierButton: (tier: string) => `.rng-tier-btn:has(.rng-tier-gem--${tier})`,\n  sideButtonHeads: \".coinflip-side-btn--heads\",\n  sideButtonTails: \".coinflip-side-btn--tails\",\n  actionButton: \".coinflip-action-btn\",\n  \n  // Lobby matches\n  matchCard: \".coinflip-match-card\",\n  matchCardOwn: \".coinflip-match-card--own\",\n  matchCardClaimable: \".coinflip-match-card--claimable\",\n  matchCardJoinBtn: \".coinflip-match-card__join-btn\",\n  \n  // Active match\n  activeMatch: \".coinflip-active-match\",\n  activeMatchWaiting: \".coinflip-active-match__waiting\",\n  activeMatchTitleWon: \".coinflip-active-match__title--won\",\n  activeMatchTitleLost: \".coinflip-active-match__title--lost\",\n  \n  // Error handling\n  errorToast: \".coinflip-error-toast\",\n  toastMessage: \".rng-toast__message\",\n  \n  // Status\n  sidebarStatus: \".coinflip-sidebar__status\",\n}\n```\n\n**Key action functions:**\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `navigateToCoinflip(page)` | Go to `/coinflip` and wait for lobby render |\n| `selectTier(page, tier)` | Click tier button, verify selection |\n| `selectSide(page, side)` | Click heads/tails, verify selection |\n| `createMatch(page, tier, side)` | Tier + side + click \"Create Game\", wait for active match |\n| `joinMatch(page, matchIndex)` | Click join on nth match card, wait for active match |\n| `cancelMatch(page)` | Click \"Cancel Match\", wait for lobby |\n| `claimOrSettle(page)` | Click claim/settle button in sidebar, wait for \"Back to Lobby\" |\n| `backToLobby(page)` | Click \"Back to Lobby\", wait for lobby |\n\n**Wait/assert primitives:**\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout)` | Poll sidebar status until text matches (e.g., \"Waiting...\", \"Complete\") |\n| `waitForResult(page, timeout)` | Wait for won/lost title class, return result string |\n| `waitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout)` | Wait for first non-claimable match card, return locator |\n| `assertLobbyEmpty(page, timeout)` | Assert zero non-claimable match cards |\n| `assertErrorToast(page, substring, timeout)` | Assert error toast visible with substring |\n| `assertNoErrorToast(page)` | Assert no error toasts |\n| `waitForLobby(page, timeout)` | Wait for lobby selector visible |\n| `trackConsoleErrors(page)` | Return `{ errors: string[], assertClean() }` — filters out browser noise |\n\n---\n\n### 3. **On-Chain Helpers** (`on-chain.ts`)\n\n**Constants:**\n```typescript\nCOINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = from CoinflipIDL.address\nPLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = from PlatformIDL.address\nFEE_BPS = 300 (3%)\n```\n\n**PDA derivation:**\n```typescript\ngetMatchPda(creator: PublicKey) → [pda, bump]  // Seeds: [\"match\", creator]\ngetConfigPda() → [pda, bump]  // Seeds: [\"coinflip_config\"]\ngetPlayerProfilePda(wallet) → [pda, bump]  // Seeds: [\"player_profile\", wallet]\n```\n\n**Program instances:**\n```typescript\ngetCoinflipProgram(connection) → Program<Coinflip>  // read-only\ngetPlatformProgram(connection) → Program<Platform>  // read-only\n```\n\n**Fetch helpers:**\n```typescript\nfetchMatch(connection, matchPda) → MatchAccount | null\nfetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda) → PlayerProfileAccount | null\ngetTreasuryAddress(connection) → PublicKey\n```\n\n**Balance helpers:**\n```typescript\ngetBalanceLamports(connection, address) → number\nsnapshotBalance(connection, address) → number  // capture for delta\n```\n\n**Fee calculation:**\n```typescript\ncalculateExpectedFee(entryAmount) → { pool, fee, payout }\n// pool = entryAmount * 2\n// fee = floor(pool * 300 / 10_000)\n// payout = pool - fee\n```\n\n**Assertion helpers:**\n\n| Function | Checks |\n|----------|--------|\n| `assertMatchCreated(conn, creator, expectedTier, expectedSide)` | Match PDA exists, phase=waiting, tier/side match, no opponent, claimed=false |\n| `assertMatchClosed(conn, matchPda)` | Match PDA no longer exists |\n| `assertTreasuryFee(conn, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)` | Treasury balance delta == calculated fee |\n| `assertPlayerProfile(conn, wallet, expected)` | Player profile stats match exact values |\n| `assertPlayerProfileDelta(conn, wallet, before, delta)` | Player profile stats changed by exact deltas |\n\n**Snapshot helpers:**\n```typescript\nsnapshotPlayerProfile(conn, wallet) → { totalGames, wins, totalWagered, totalWon }\n// Returns zeros if profile doesn't exist\n```\n\n**Account types:**\n```typescript\ninterface MatchAccount {\n  creator, opponent: PublicKey\n  tier: number\n  entryAmount: { toNumber() }\n  creatorSide: number (0=heads, 1=tails)\n  phase: Record<string, object>  // { waiting } | { locked } | { complete }\n  result: number\n  winner: PublicKey\n  claimed: boolean\n  createdAt, lockedAt, resolveDeadline: { toNumber() }\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey\n  bump: number\n}\n\ninterface PlayerProfileAccount {\n  authority: PublicKey\n  totalGames, wins, totalWagered, totalWon: { toNumber() }\n  bump: number\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Wallet Helpers** (`wallets.ts`)\n\n**Deterministic keypairs:**\n```typescript\nPLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(0xaa...aa)  // 32 bytes of 0xaa\nPLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(0xbb...bb)  // 32 bytes of 0xbb\nLOCAL_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"\nDEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL = 10\n```\n\n**Funding functions:**\n```typescript\nfundWallet(connection, to, solAmount = 10) → Promise<void>\n// Airdrop + confirm\n\nfundTestWallets(rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL, solAmount = 10) \n  → Promise<{ playerA, playerB: Keypair; connection }>\n// Funds both + sanity checks balances >= expected\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Lifecycle Test** (`lifecycle.spec.ts`)\n\n**Pattern:**\n1. `beforeAll`: Fund wallets, initialize localnet (configs)\n2. Player A creates match (iron, heads) → verify on-chain match PDA exists\n3. Player B navigates, sees match in lobby, joins → active match appears\n4. Snapshot treasury + player profiles\n5. Wait for result (VRF pre-fulfilled HEADS → creator wins)\n6. Verify results: A won, B lost\n7. Player A claims → match PDA closes\n8. Verify treasury fee delta\n9. Verify player profile deltas (games, wins, wagered, won)\n10. Player A returns to lobby\n11. Assert no console errors\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Use `.toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 })` for UI waits\n- Mix UI assertions with on-chain snapshots + deltas\n- Use `Promise.all()` to parallelize independent waits\n- Track console errors with `po.trackConsoleErrors(page)` and `consoleA.assertClean()`\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Cancel-Flow Test** (`cancel-flow.spec.ts`)\n\n**Pattern:**\n1. `beforeAll`: Fund wallets, initialize localnet\n2. Navigate to coinflip, snapshot balance before\n3. Create match → verify match PDA exists, waiting phase\n4. Balance after create < balance before (entry + rent + fee)\n5. Cancel match → lobby visible, no matches\n6. Verify match PDA closed\n7. Balance after cancel > balance after create (refund received)\n8. Net cost < 10M lamports (just tx fees for create + cancel)\n9. Recreate with different side (iron, tails) → same PDA address, new side\n10. Cancel second match to clean up\n11. Assert no console errors\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Balance snapshots before/after to verify refunds\n- Same PDA address reused on recreate (seeds = [\"match\", creator])\n- Verify both UI transitions and on-chain account lifecycle\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Localnet Setup** (`localnet-setup.ts`)\n\n**Deterministic admin/treasury keypairs:**\n```typescript\nADMIN = Keypair.fromSeed(0xdd...dd)\nTREASURY = Keypair.fromSeed(0xcc...cc)\n```\n\n**Setup function:**\n```typescript\ninitializeLocalnet(rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL) → Promise<void>\n```\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Fund admin and treasury (2 SOL each)\n2. Create Anchor providers with admin keypair\n3. Check if coinflip config PDA exists\n   - If not, call `initializeConfig(treasury)` instruction\n4. Check if platform config PDA exists\n   - If not, call `initializePlatform(treasury)` instruction\n5. Idempotent — silently succeeds if configs already exist\n\n**Helper:**\n```typescript\nfundIfNeeded(connection, pubkey, solAmount)\n// Only airdrop if balance < solAmount SOL\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Patterns for Error Flows\n\nBased on the infrastructure, here's how to structure error-flow tests:\n\n### Structure:\n```typescript\ntest(\"error scenario: [description]\", async ({\n  playerAPage,\n  playerBPage,\n  connection,\n}) => {\n  const consoleA = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerAPage);\n  const consoleB = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerBPage);\n\n  // Setup: navigate\n  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerAPage);\n  \n  // Try action that should error\n  await po.createMatch(playerAPage, \"iron\", \"heads\");\n  \n  // Assert error toast with substring\n  await po.assertErrorToast(playerAPage, \"expected error text\", 5_000);\n  \n  // Verify on-chain state is clean (no partial state)\n  // e.g., match PDA should not exist if creation failed\n  \n  // Cleanup assertions\n  consoleA.assertClean();\n  consoleB.assertClean();\n});\n```\n\n### Common error assertions:\n- **UI toast**: `assertErrorToast(page, substring)`\n- **No toast**: `assertNoErrorToast(page)`\n- **PDA not created**: `await fetchMatch(conn, pda)` returns null\n- **Account remains closed**: `assertMatchClosed(conn, pda)`\n- **Balance unchanged**: snapshot before, check after equals before\n- **No console errors**: `trackConsoleErrors(page).assertClean()`\n\nThis infrastructure is solid for comprehensive error-flow testing across UI, on-chain state, and console hygiene."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a74da68fc480a73f3 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 47851\ntool_uses: 7\nduration_ms: 33895</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9011bcd3-c1e3-4ba2-996b-dc56e2b15fd6","uuid":"3f532c2c-d30a-4a22-bdcf-bea56a726159","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the E2E local test infrastructure for the rng-utopia project. I need to understand:\n\n1. The fixtures in `apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` - what fixtures are available (playerAContext, playerBContext, connection, etc.)\n2. The page-object helpers in `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts` - especially `assertErrorToast()`, `createMatch()`, `joinMatch()`, `claimOrSettle()`, `cancelMatch()`, selectors\n3. The on-chain helpers in `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` - especially `fetchMatch()`, `assertMatchCreated()`\n4. The wallet helpers in `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` - PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B keypairs, funding functions\n5. The existing lifecycle test in `apps/platform/e2e/local/lifecycle.spec.ts` - how it's structured, what patterns it uses\n6. The cancel-flow test in `apps/platform/e2e/local/cancel-flow.spec.ts` - patterns used\n7. The localnet-setup helper in `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts`\n\nRead ALL of these files completely. I need the full content to implement error-flow tests.\n\nRoot path: /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/","agentId":"a74da68fc480a73f3","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the E2E infrastructure files. Let me provide you with a comprehensive overview.\n\n---\n\n## E2E Local Test Infrastructure Summary\n\n### 1. **Fixtures** (`fixtures.ts`)\n\n**Available fixtures:**\n- `playerAPage` / `playerBPage` — isolated Playwright `Page` instances in separate browser contexts\n- `playerAContext` / `playerBContext` — isolated `BrowserContext` instances\n- `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair` — deterministic keypairs (read-only)\n- `connection` — shared `Connection` to the local RPC (confirmed commitment)\n\n**How it works:**\n- Creates isolated browser contexts via `createPlayerContext()` which injects `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` before page loads\n- The seed is the raw 32-byte array from each player's keypair\n- `TestWalletProvider` reads this seed at React render time to construct the correct `Keypair`\n- Each context has its own storage/session — zero cross-contamination\n\n**Usage pattern:**\n```typescript\ntest(\"name\", async ({ playerAPage, playerBPage, connection }) => { ... })\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Page-Object Helpers** (`page-objects.ts`)\n\n**Selectors:**\n```typescript\nsel = {\n  // Lobby structure\n  lobby: \".coinflip-lobby\",\n  sidebar: \".coinflip-sidebar\",\n  main: \".coinflip-main\",\n  \n  // Create flow\n  tierButton: (tier: string) => `.rng-tier-btn:has(.rng-tier-gem--${tier})`,\n  sideButtonHeads: \".coinflip-side-btn--heads\",\n  sideButtonTails: \".coinflip-side-btn--tails\",\n  actionButton: \".coinflip-action-btn\",\n  \n  // Lobby matches\n  matchCard: \".coinflip-match-card\",\n  matchCardOwn: \".coinflip-match-card--own\",\n  matchCardClaimable: \".coinflip-match-card--claimable\",\n  matchCardJoinBtn: \".coinflip-match-card__join-btn\",\n  \n  // Active match\n  activeMatch: \".coinflip-active-match\",\n  activeMatchWaiting: \".coinflip-active-match__waiting\",\n  activeMatchTitleWon: \".coinflip-active-match__title--won\",\n  activeMatchTitleLost: \".coinflip-active-match__title--lost\",\n  \n  // Error handling\n  errorToast: \".coinflip-error-toast\",\n  toastMessage: \".rng-toast__message\",\n  \n  // Status\n  sidebarStatus: \".coinflip-sidebar__status\",\n}\n```\n\n**Key action functions:**\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `navigateToCoinflip(page)` | Go to `/coinflip` and wait for lobby render |\n| `selectTier(page, tier)` | Click tier button, verify selection |\n| `selectSide(page, side)` | Click heads/tails, verify selection |\n| `createMatch(page, tier, side)` | Tier + side + click \"Create Game\", wait for active match |\n| `joinMatch(page, matchIndex)` | Click join on nth match card, wait for active match |\n| `cancelMatch(page)` | Click \"Cancel Match\", wait for lobby |\n| `claimOrSettle(page)` | Click claim/settle button in sidebar, wait for \"Back to Lobby\" |\n| `backToLobby(page)` | Click \"Back to Lobby\", wait for lobby |\n\n**Wait/assert primitives:**\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout)` | Poll sidebar status until text matches (e.g., \"Waiting...\", \"Complete\") |\n| `waitForResult(page, timeout)` | Wait for won/lost title class, return result string |\n| `waitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout)` | Wait for first non-claimable match card, return locator |\n| `assertLobbyEmpty(page, timeout)` | Assert zero non-claimable match cards |\n| `assertErrorToast(page, substring, timeout)` | Assert error toast visible with substring |\n| `assertNoErrorToast(page)` | Assert no error toasts |\n| `waitForLobby(page, timeout)` | Wait for lobby selector visible |\n| `trackConsoleErrors(page)` | Return `{ errors: string[], assertClean() }` — filters out browser noise |\n\n---\n\n### 3. **On-Chain Helpers** (`on-chain.ts`)\n\n**Constants:**\n```typescript\nCOINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = from CoinflipIDL.address\nPLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = from PlatformIDL.address\nFEE_BPS = 300 (3%)\n```\n\n**PDA derivation:**\n```typescript\ngetMatchPda(creator: PublicKey) → [pda, bump]  // Seeds: [\"match\", creator]\ngetConfigPda() → [pda, bump]  // Seeds: [\"coinflip_config\"]\ngetPlayerProfilePda(wallet) → [pda, bump]  // Seeds: [\"player_profile\", wallet]\n```\n\n**Program instances:**\n```typescript\ngetCoinflipProgram(connection) → Program<Coinflip>  // read-only\ngetPlatformProgram(connection) → Program<Platform>  // read-only\n```\n\n**Fetch helpers:**\n```typescript\nfetchMatch(connection, matchPda) → MatchAccount | null\nfetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda) → PlayerProfileAccount | null\ngetTreasuryAddress(connection) → PublicKey\n```\n\n**Balance helpers:**\n```typescript\ngetBalanceLamports(connection, address) → number\nsnapshotBalance(connection, address) → number  // capture for delta\n```\n\n**Fee calculation:**\n```typescript\ncalculateExpectedFee(entryAmount) → { pool, fee, payout }\n// pool = entryAmount * 2\n// fee = floor(pool * 300 / 10_000)\n// payout = pool - fee\n```\n\n**Assertion helpers:**\n\n| Function | Checks |\n|----------|--------|\n| `assertMatchCreated(conn, creator, expectedTier, expectedSide)` | Match PDA exists, phase=waiting, tier/side match, no opponent, claimed=false |\n| `assertMatchClosed(conn, matchPda)` | Match PDA no longer exists |\n| `assertTreasuryFee(conn, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)` | Treasury balance delta == calculated fee |\n| `assertPlayerProfile(conn, wallet, expected)` | Player profile stats match exact values |\n| `assertPlayerProfileDelta(conn, wallet, before, delta)` | Player profile stats changed by exact deltas |\n\n**Snapshot helpers:**\n```typescript\nsnapshotPlayerProfile(conn, wallet) → { totalGames, wins, totalWagered, totalWon }\n// Returns zeros if profile doesn't exist\n```\n\n**Account types:**\n```typescript\ninterface MatchAccount {\n  creator, opponent: PublicKey\n  tier: number\n  entryAmount: { toNumber() }\n  creatorSide: number (0=heads, 1=tails)\n  phase: Record<string, object>  // { waiting } | { locked } | { complete }\n  result: number\n  winner: PublicKey\n  claimed: boolean\n  createdAt, lockedAt, resolveDeadline: { toNumber() }\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey\n  bump: number\n}\n\ninterface PlayerProfileAccount {\n  authority: PublicKey\n  totalGames, wins, totalWagered, totalWon: { toNumber() }\n  bump: number\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Wallet Helpers** (`wallets.ts`)\n\n**Deterministic keypairs:**\n```typescript\nPLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(0xaa...aa)  // 32 bytes of 0xaa\nPLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(0xbb...bb)  // 32 bytes of 0xbb\nLOCAL_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"\nDEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL = 10\n```\n\n**Funding functions:**\n```typescript\nfundWallet(connection, to, solAmount = 10) → Promise<void>\n// Airdrop + confirm\n\nfundTestWallets(rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL, solAmount = 10) \n  → Promise<{ playerA, playerB: Keypair; connection }>\n// Funds both + sanity checks balances >= expected\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Lifecycle Test** (`lifecycle.spec.ts`)\n\n**Pattern:**\n1. `beforeAll`: Fund wallets, initialize localnet (configs)\n2. Player A creates match (iron, heads) → verify on-chain match PDA exists\n3. Player B navigates, sees match in lobby, joins → active match appears\n4. Snapshot treasury + player profiles\n5. Wait for result (VRF pre-fulfilled HEADS → creator wins)\n6. Verify results: A won, B lost\n7. Player A claims → match PDA closes\n8. Verify treasury fee delta\n9. Verify player profile deltas (games, wins, wagered, won)\n10. Player A returns to lobby\n11. Assert no console errors\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Use `.toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 })` for UI waits\n- Mix UI assertions with on-chain snapshots + deltas\n- Use `Promise.all()` to parallelize independent waits\n- Track console errors with `po.trackConsoleErrors(page)` and `consoleA.assertClean()`\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Cancel-Flow Test** (`cancel-flow.spec.ts`)\n\n**Pattern:**\n1. `beforeAll`: Fund wallets, initialize localnet\n2. Navigate to coinflip, snapshot balance before\n3. Create match → verify match PDA exists, waiting phase\n4. Balance after create < balance before (entry + rent + fee)\n5. Cancel match → lobby visible, no matches\n6. Verify match PDA closed\n7. Balance after cancel > balance after create (refund received)\n8. Net cost < 10M lamports (just tx fees for create + cancel)\n9. Recreate with different side (iron, tails) → same PDA address, new side\n10. Cancel second match to clean up\n11. Assert no console errors\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Balance snapshots before/after to verify refunds\n- Same PDA address reused on recreate (seeds = [\"match\", creator])\n- Verify both UI transitions and on-chain account lifecycle\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Localnet Setup** (`localnet-setup.ts`)\n\n**Deterministic admin/treasury keypairs:**\n```typescript\nADMIN = Keypair.fromSeed(0xdd...dd)\nTREASURY = Keypair.fromSeed(0xcc...cc)\n```\n\n**Setup function:**\n```typescript\ninitializeLocalnet(rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL) → Promise<void>\n```\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Fund admin and treasury (2 SOL each)\n2. Create Anchor providers with admin keypair\n3. Check if coinflip config PDA exists\n   - If not, call `initializeConfig(treasury)` instruction\n4. Check if platform config PDA exists\n   - If not, call `initializePlatform(treasury)` instruction\n5. Idempotent — silently succeeds if configs already exist\n\n**Helper:**\n```typescript\nfundIfNeeded(connection, pubkey, solAmount)\n// Only airdrop if balance < solAmount SOL\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Patterns for Error Flows\n\nBased on the infrastructure, here's how to structure error-flow tests:\n\n### Structure:\n```typescript\ntest(\"error scenario: [description]\", async ({\n  playerAPage,\n  playerBPage,\n  connection,\n}) => {\n  const consoleA = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerAPage);\n  const consoleB = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerBPage);\n\n  // Setup: navigate\n  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerAPage);\n  \n  // Try action that should error\n  await po.createMatch(playerAPage, \"iron\", \"heads\");\n  \n  // Assert error toast with substring\n  await po.assertErrorToast(playerAPage, \"expected error text\", 5_000);\n  \n  // Verify on-chain state is clean (no partial state)\n  // e.g., match PDA should not exist if creation failed\n  \n  // Cleanup assertions\n  consoleA.assertClean();\n  consoleB.assertClean();\n});\n```\n\n### Common error assertions:\n- **UI toast**: `assertErrorToast(page, substring)`\n- **No toast**: `assertNoErrorToast(page)`\n- **PDA not created**: `await fetchMatch(conn, pda)` returns null\n- **Account remains closed**: `assertMatchClosed(conn, pda)`\n- **Balance unchanged**: snapshot before, check after equals before\n- **No console errors**: `trackConsoleErrors(page).assertClean()`\n\nThis infrastructure is solid for comprehensive error-flow testing across UI, on-chain state, and console hygiene."}],"totalDurationMs":33895,"totalTokens":47851,"totalToolUseCount":7,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19803,"cache_read_input_tokens":24809,"output_tokens":3232,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":19803,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
