{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VpNLGkQCRfw2LavP3xMSER","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary by compiling all the information I've gathered:\n\n## Exploration Report: Coinflip UI Error Handling & Notification System\n\nI've thoroughly explored the coinflip UI error handling system. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Error Handling Architecture**\n\n**Error State Management** (`CoinflipContext.tsx`, lines 95-97, 140-141):\n- Errors are stored in context state: `error: string | null`\n- Function to clear: `clearError: () => void`\n- All transaction/operation errors flow through the context\n\n**Error Parsing Function** (`CoinflipContext.tsx`, lines 28-77):\nThe system uses `parseTransactionError()` which converts Solana/wallet errors into user-friendly messages:\n\n```typescript\nfunction parseTransactionError(err: unknown): string {\n  // Wallet not connected\n  if (msg.includes(\"Wallet not connected\")) → \"Wallet not connected. Please connect your wallet first.\"\n  \n  // User rejected transaction\n  if (msg.includes(\"User rejected\")) → \"Transaction cancelled by user.\"\n  \n  // Insufficient balance (MAIN ERROR FOR CREATING MATCH)\n  if (msg.includes(\"insufficient lamports\") || msg.includes(\"Insufficient funds\") || msg.includes(\"0x1\"))\n    → \"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL to complete this transaction.\"\n  \n  // Match already exists\n  if (msg.includes(\"already in use\"))\n    → \"You already have an active match. Cancel it before creating a new one.\"\n  \n  // Network errors\n  if (msg.includes(\"Failed to fetch\") || msg.includes(\"NetworkError\"))\n    → \"Network error. Please check your connection and try again.\"\n  \n  // Anchor program errors\n  if (msg.includes(\"InvalidPhase\"))\n    → \"This match is no longer available.\"\n  if (msg.includes(\"CannotJoinOwnMatch\"))\n    → \"You cannot join your own match.\"\n  \n  // Simulation failures\n  if (msg.includes(\"Simulation failed\"))\n    → \"Transaction simulation failed. The match may no longer be available.\"\n  \n  // Blockhash expiry\n  if (msg.includes(\"blockhash not found\"))\n    → \"Transaction expired. Please try again.\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **2. Error Display in UI**\n\n**Display Method** (`CoinflipPage.tsx`, lines 436-442):\n```jsx\n{error && createPortal(\n  <div className=\"coinflip-error-toast\">\n    <Toast variant=\"error\" message={error} onClose={clearError} />\n  </div>,\n  document.body\n)}\n```\n\n- Errors are rendered as a **portal to document.body** (fixed position)\n- Uses the shared `Toast` component from `@rng-utopia/ui`\n- Toast is closeable via `clearError()` callback\n\n---\n\n### **3. Specific Error Scenarios**\n\n**A. Insufficient Balance (Creating Match)**\n- **Location**: `CoinflipContext.tsx`, line 43\n- **Error Message**: `\"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL to complete this transaction.\"`\n- **Trigger**: When trying to `createMatch()` and wallet balance is too low\n- **Flow**: \n  1. User clicks \"Create Game\"\n  2. `createMatch()` is called\n  3. Transaction fails with \"insufficient lamports\" error\n  4. `parseTransactionError()` converts it\n  5. `setError()` displays the toast\n  6. User can close with X button\n\n**B. Joining a Locked/Completed Match**\n- **Location**: `CoinflipContext.tsx`, line 57-58\n- **Error Message**: `\"This match is no longer available.\"`\n- **Trigger**: When match phase is invalid (InvalidPhase anchor error)\n- **Flow**:\n  1. User clicks \"Join\" on a match\n  2. Match is fetched to verify it exists\n  3. If match state changed (e.g., already started or completed), anchor instruction returns `InvalidPhase` error\n  4. Error is parsed and displayed\n\n**C. Joining Own Match**\n- **Location**: `CoinflipContext.tsx`, line 61\n- **Error Message**: `\"You cannot join your own match.\"`\n- **Trigger**: Anchor validation prevents self-join\n- **Note**: This is caught at instruction level, not pre-checked in UI\n\n**D. Already Has Active Match**\n- **Location**: `CoinflipContext.tsx`, lines 48, 284-295\n- **Error Message**: `\"You already have an active match. Cancel it before creating a new one.\"` OR `\"Settle your previous match first.\"`\n- **Trigger**: When calling `createMatch()` if user already has an unclosed match PDA\n- **Special Handling** (lines 284-295):\n  - Pre-checks if match PDA already exists on-chain\n  - If it exists and is settled → shows match UI + \"Settle your previous match first.\"\n  - If it exists and in-progress → shows match UI + \"You already have an active match.\"\n\n---\n\n### **4. Toast/Notification Component**\n\n**Toast Component** (`packages/ui/src/components/Toast.tsx`):\n```typescript\nexport interface ToastProps {\n  variant: \"success\" | \"error\" | \"warning\" | \"info\";\n  message: ReactNode;\n  onClose?: () => void;\n}\n\nexport function Toast({ variant, message, onClose }: ToastProps) {\n  return (\n    <div className={`rng-toast rng-toast--${variant}`} role=\"alert\">\n      <span className=\"rng-toast__message\">{message}</span>\n      {onClose && (\n        <button className=\"rng-toast__close\" onClick={onClose}>\n          &times;\n        </button>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **5. CSS Classes & Styling**\n\n**Toast CSS Classes** (`apps/platform/src/index.css`, lines 5042-5075):\n\n```css\n/* Base Toast */\n.rng-toast {\n  font-family: var(--font-pixel);\n  font-size: 0.625rem;\n  padding: 0.75rem 1rem;\n  border: 2px solid;\n}\n\n/* Error Variant */\n.rng-toast--error {\n  background: rgba(240, 184, 32, 0.1);  /* Semi-transparent gold background */\n  border-color: var(--color-error);      /* #cc4444 (red) */\n  color: var(--color-error);             /* Red text */\n  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);\n}\n\n/* Success Variant (for reference) */\n.rng-toast--success {\n  background: rgba(69, 176, 88, 0.1);    /* Semi-transparent green */\n  border-color: var(--color-success);    /* #44aa44 */\n  color: var(--color-success);\n  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);\n}\n\n/* Warning Variant (for reference) */\n.rng-toast--warning {\n  background: rgba(249, 240, 2, 0.1);\n  border-color: var(--color-warning);    /* #f0b820 */\n  color: var(--color-warning);\n  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);\n}\n\n/* Info Variant (for reference) */\n.rng-toast--info {\n  background: rgba(160, 184, 208, 0.1);\n  border-color: var(--color-neon-cyan);  /* #4488cc */\n  color: var(--color-neon-cyan);\n  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);\n}\n```\n\n**Error Toast Container** (`apps/platform/src/index.css`, lines 5856-5876):\n\n```css\n.coinflip-error-toast {\n  position: fixed;\n  left: 50%;\n  top: calc(86% + 0.35rem);              /* Fixed position near bottom */\n  transform: translateX(-50%);            /* Center horizontally */\n  width: min(920px, 62vw);\n  z-index: 12;\n  pointer-events: none;                   /* Transparent to clicks unless on toast itself */\n}\n\n.coinflip-error-toast .rng-toast {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: space-between;\n  gap: 0.75rem;\n  pointer-events: auto;                   /* Toast itself is clickable */\n}\n\n.coinflip-error-toast .rng-toast__message {\n  flex: 1;\n}\n```\n\n**Color Variables Used**:\n- `--color-error: #cc4444` (Red)\n- `--color-error-glow: rgba(204, 68, 68, 0.2)` (Red glow, not used here)\n\n---\n\n### **6. Error Flow for Each Scenario**\n\n**Scenario 1: Insufficient Balance on Create Match**\n```\nUser clicks \"Create Game\"\n  ↓\ncreateMatch() in context\n  ↓\nbuildCreateMatchTx() builds instruction\n  ↓\nsendAndConfirm() sends tx to wallet\n  ↓\nWallet signs, Solana runtime rejects (insufficient lamports)\n  ↓\ncatch block in createMatch()\n  ↓\nparseTransactionError() → \"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL...\"\n  ↓\nsetError(parsedMessage)\n  ↓\nCoinflipPage.tsx renders toast portal with error\n  ↓\nUser sees RED bordered toast at bottom with X button\n```\n\n**Scenario 2: Joining Locked Match**\n```\nUser clicks \"Join\" on match\n  ↓\njoinMatch(matchId) in context\n  ↓\nfetchMatch() to verify match exists\n  ↓\nbuildJoinMatchTx() builds instruction\n  ↓\nsendAndConfirm() sends tx\n  ↓\nAnchor program rejects (InvalidPhase)\n  ↓\ncatch block in joinMatch()\n  ↓\nparseTransactionError() → \"This match is no longer available.\"\n  ↓\nsetError(parsedMessage)\n  ↓\nRED toast displays\n```\n\n**Scenario 3: Claiming Without Permission**\n```\nUser clicks \"Claim Payout\"\n  ↓\nclaimPayout() in context\n  ↓\nbuildClaimPayoutTx() with caller = user's publicKey\n  ↓\nsendAndConfirm() sends tx\n  ↓\nAnchor program validates winner on-chain\n  ↓\nIf caller != winner, instruction fails\n  ↓\nAnchor error returned to user\n  ↓\nparseTransactionError() catches generic error\n  ↓\nGeneric fallback: \"Transaction failed: [truncated error]...\"\n  ↓\nRED toast displays\n```\n\n---\n\n### **7. Key Implementation Details**\n\n**Where Errors Are Caught** (CoinflipContext.tsx):\n- `createMatch()` - lines 319-320\n- `joinMatch()` - lines 364-365\n- `cancelMatch()` - lines 386-387\n- `timeoutCancel()` - lines 415-429\n- `claimPayout()` - lines 465-466\n\n**When Errors Are Cleared**:\n- Explicitly: User clicks X button on toast\n- Automatically: Before new operation starts (e.g., `setError(null)` on line 279 before creating)\n\n**Error Context Clearing**:\n- Line 141: `clearError = useCallback(() => setError(null), [])`\n- Passed to Toast component via `onClose={clearError}`\n\n---\n\n### **8. File Structure & Locations**\n\n| Component | File Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| Error Context | `/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` | Error state management + parsing |\n| Page Component | `/pages/CoinflipPage.tsx` | Error toast rendering |\n| Toast Component | `/packages/ui/src/components/Toast.tsx` | Reusable toast UI |\n| CSS Styles | `/apps/platform/src/index.css` | Toast & error-toast styling |\n\n---\n\n### **Summary**\n\nThe coinflip UI uses a **context-based error system** with:\n- **Central error state** in CoinflipContext\n- **Smart error parsing** that converts Solana/Anchor errors to user-friendly messages\n- **Portal-based toast rendering** (fixed at bottom center)\n- **Visual distinction** with red border + gold-tinted background for errors\n- **User control** to dismiss via X button\n- **Specific messages** for insufficient balance, locked matches, ownership conflicts, etc.\n\nThe system gracefully handles all three error scenarios you asked about with specific, helpful error messages."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1158cff1b294e3ff (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 71735\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 78060</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9011bcd3-c1e3-4ba2-996b-dc56e2b15fd6","uuid":"1bc1c004-a946-456e-b896-6b772ef710cb","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how error messages are displayed in the coinflip UI. Explore:\n\n1. How does the UI show errors when creating a match with insufficient balance?\n2. How does the UI show errors when joining a locked match?\n3. How does the UI show errors when someone tries to claim who shouldn't?\n4. Look at the error/toast/notification system - search for toast, error, notification patterns in:\n   - `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/` (all files)\n   - `apps/platform/src/components/` (toast/notification components)\n   - `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx`\n   - `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`\n\nAlso look at what CSS classes or selectors are used for error messages (e.g., `.error-toast`, `.toast`, notification classes).\n\nRoot path: /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/","agentId":"a1158cff1b294e3ff","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary by compiling all the information I've gathered:\n\n## Exploration Report: Coinflip UI Error Handling & Notification System\n\nI've thoroughly explored the coinflip UI error handling system. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Error Handling Architecture**\n\n**Error State Management** (`CoinflipContext.tsx`, lines 95-97, 140-141):\n- Errors are stored in context state: `error: string | null`\n- Function to clear: `clearError: () => void`\n- All transaction/operation errors flow through the context\n\n**Error Parsing Function** (`CoinflipContext.tsx`, lines 28-77):\nThe system uses `parseTransactionError()` which converts Solana/wallet errors into user-friendly messages:\n\n```typescript\nfunction parseTransactionError(err: unknown): string {\n  // Wallet not connected\n  if (msg.includes(\"Wallet not connected\")) → \"Wallet not connected. Please connect your wallet first.\"\n  \n  // User rejected transaction\n  if (msg.includes(\"User rejected\")) → \"Transaction cancelled by user.\"\n  \n  // Insufficient balance (MAIN ERROR FOR CREATING MATCH)\n  if (msg.includes(\"insufficient lamports\") || msg.includes(\"Insufficient funds\") || msg.includes(\"0x1\"))\n    → \"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL to complete this transaction.\"\n  \n  // Match already exists\n  if (msg.includes(\"already in use\"))\n    → \"You already have an active match. Cancel it before creating a new one.\"\n  \n  // Network errors\n  if (msg.includes(\"Failed to fetch\") || msg.includes(\"NetworkError\"))\n    → \"Network error. Please check your connection and try again.\"\n  \n  // Anchor program errors\n  if (msg.includes(\"InvalidPhase\"))\n    → \"This match is no longer available.\"\n  if (msg.includes(\"CannotJoinOwnMatch\"))\n    → \"You cannot join your own match.\"\n  \n  // Simulation failures\n  if (msg.includes(\"Simulation failed\"))\n    → \"Transaction simulation failed. The match may no longer be available.\"\n  \n  // Blockhash expiry\n  if (msg.includes(\"blockhash not found\"))\n    → \"Transaction expired. Please try again.\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **2. Error Display in UI**\n\n**Display Method** (`CoinflipPage.tsx`, lines 436-442):\n```jsx\n{error && createPortal(\n  <div className=\"coinflip-error-toast\">\n    <Toast variant=\"error\" message={error} onClose={clearError} />\n  </div>,\n  document.body\n)}\n```\n\n- Errors are rendered as a **portal to document.body** (fixed position)\n- Uses the shared `Toast` component from `@rng-utopia/ui`\n- Toast is closeable via `clearError()` callback\n\n---\n\n### **3. Specific Error Scenarios**\n\n**A. Insufficient Balance (Creating Match)**\n- **Location**: `CoinflipContext.tsx`, line 43\n- **Error Message**: `\"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL to complete this transaction.\"`\n- **Trigger**: When trying to `createMatch()` and wallet balance is too low\n- **Flow**: \n  1. User clicks \"Create Game\"\n  2. `createMatch()` is called\n  3. Transaction fails with \"insufficient lamports\" error\n  4. `parseTransactionError()` converts it\n  5. `setError()` displays the toast\n  6. User can close with X button\n\n**B. Joining a Locked/Completed Match**\n- **Location**: `CoinflipContext.tsx`, line 57-58\n- **Error Message**: `\"This match is no longer available.\"`\n- **Trigger**: When match phase is invalid (InvalidPhase anchor error)\n- **Flow**:\n  1. User clicks \"Join\" on a match\n  2. Match is fetched to verify it exists\n  3. If match state changed (e.g., already started or completed), anchor instruction returns `InvalidPhase` error\n  4. Error is parsed and displayed\n\n**C. Joining Own Match**\n- **Location**: `CoinflipContext.tsx`, line 61\n- **Error Message**: `\"You cannot join your own match.\"`\n- **Trigger**: Anchor validation prevents self-join\n- **Note**: This is caught at instruction level, not pre-checked in UI\n\n**D. Already Has Active Match**\n- **Location**: `CoinflipContext.tsx`, lines 48, 284-295\n- **Error Message**: `\"You already have an active match. Cancel it before creating a new one.\"` OR `\"Settle your previous match first.\"`\n- **Trigger**: When calling `createMatch()` if user already has an unclosed match PDA\n- **Special Handling** (lines 284-295):\n  - Pre-checks if match PDA already exists on-chain\n  - If it exists and is settled → shows match UI + \"Settle your previous match first.\"\n  - If it exists and in-progress → shows match UI + \"You already have an active match.\"\n\n---\n\n### **4. Toast/Notification Component**\n\n**Toast Component** (`packages/ui/src/components/Toast.tsx`):\n```typescript\nexport interface ToastProps {\n  variant: \"success\" | \"error\" | \"warning\" | \"info\";\n  message: ReactNode;\n  onClose?: () => void;\n}\n\nexport function Toast({ variant, message, onClose }: ToastProps) {\n  return (\n    <div className={`rng-toast rng-toast--${variant}`} role=\"alert\">\n      <span className=\"rng-toast__message\">{message}</span>\n      {onClose && (\n        <button className=\"rng-toast__close\" onClick={onClose}>\n          &times;\n        </button>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **5. CSS Classes & Styling**\n\n**Toast CSS Classes** (`apps/platform/src/index.css`, lines 5042-5075):\n\n```css\n/* Base Toast */\n.rng-toast {\n  font-family: var(--font-pixel);\n  font-size: 0.625rem;\n  padding: 0.75rem 1rem;\n  border: 2px solid;\n}\n\n/* Error Variant */\n.rng-toast--error {\n  background: rgba(240, 184, 32, 0.1);  /* Semi-transparent gold background */\n  border-color: var(--color-error);      /* #cc4444 (red) */\n  color: var(--color-error);             /* Red text */\n  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);\n}\n\n/* Success Variant (for reference) */\n.rng-toast--success {\n  background: rgba(69, 176, 88, 0.1);    /* Semi-transparent green */\n  border-color: var(--color-success);    /* #44aa44 */\n  color: var(--color-success);\n  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);\n}\n\n/* Warning Variant (for reference) */\n.rng-toast--warning {\n  background: rgba(249, 240, 2, 0.1);\n  border-color: var(--color-warning);    /* #f0b820 */\n  color: var(--color-warning);\n  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);\n}\n\n/* Info Variant (for reference) */\n.rng-toast--info {\n  background: rgba(160, 184, 208, 0.1);\n  border-color: var(--color-neon-cyan);  /* #4488cc */\n  color: var(--color-neon-cyan);\n  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);\n}\n```\n\n**Error Toast Container** (`apps/platform/src/index.css`, lines 5856-5876):\n\n```css\n.coinflip-error-toast {\n  position: fixed;\n  left: 50%;\n  top: calc(86% + 0.35rem);              /* Fixed position near bottom */\n  transform: translateX(-50%);            /* Center horizontally */\n  width: min(920px, 62vw);\n  z-index: 12;\n  pointer-events: none;                   /* Transparent to clicks unless on toast itself */\n}\n\n.coinflip-error-toast .rng-toast {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: space-between;\n  gap: 0.75rem;\n  pointer-events: auto;                   /* Toast itself is clickable */\n}\n\n.coinflip-error-toast .rng-toast__message {\n  flex: 1;\n}\n```\n\n**Color Variables Used**:\n- `--color-error: #cc4444` (Red)\n- `--color-error-glow: rgba(204, 68, 68, 0.2)` (Red glow, not used here)\n\n---\n\n### **6. Error Flow for Each Scenario**\n\n**Scenario 1: Insufficient Balance on Create Match**\n```\nUser clicks \"Create Game\"\n  ↓\ncreateMatch() in context\n  ↓\nbuildCreateMatchTx() builds instruction\n  ↓\nsendAndConfirm() sends tx to wallet\n  ↓\nWallet signs, Solana runtime rejects (insufficient lamports)\n  ↓\ncatch block in createMatch()\n  ↓\nparseTransactionError() → \"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL...\"\n  ↓\nsetError(parsedMessage)\n  ↓\nCoinflipPage.tsx renders toast portal with error\n  ↓\nUser sees RED bordered toast at bottom with X button\n```\n\n**Scenario 2: Joining Locked Match**\n```\nUser clicks \"Join\" on match\n  ↓\njoinMatch(matchId) in context\n  ↓\nfetchMatch() to verify match exists\n  ↓\nbuildJoinMatchTx() builds instruction\n  ↓\nsendAndConfirm() sends tx\n  ↓\nAnchor program rejects (InvalidPhase)\n  ↓\ncatch block in joinMatch()\n  ↓\nparseTransactionError() → \"This match is no longer available.\"\n  ↓\nsetError(parsedMessage)\n  ↓\nRED toast displays\n```\n\n**Scenario 3: Claiming Without Permission**\n```\nUser clicks \"Claim Payout\"\n  ↓\nclaimPayout() in context\n  ↓\nbuildClaimPayoutTx() with caller = user's publicKey\n  ↓\nsendAndConfirm() sends tx\n  ↓\nAnchor program validates winner on-chain\n  ↓\nIf caller != winner, instruction fails\n  ↓\nAnchor error returned to user\n  ↓\nparseTransactionError() catches generic error\n  ↓\nGeneric fallback: \"Transaction failed: [truncated error]...\"\n  ↓\nRED toast displays\n```\n\n---\n\n### **7. Key Implementation Details**\n\n**Where Errors Are Caught** (CoinflipContext.tsx):\n- `createMatch()` - lines 319-320\n- `joinMatch()` - lines 364-365\n- `cancelMatch()` - lines 386-387\n- `timeoutCancel()` - lines 415-429\n- `claimPayout()` - lines 465-466\n\n**When Errors Are Cleared**:\n- Explicitly: User clicks X button on toast\n- Automatically: Before new operation starts (e.g., `setError(null)` on line 279 before creating)\n\n**Error Context Clearing**:\n- Line 141: `clearError = useCallback(() => setError(null), [])`\n- Passed to Toast component via `onClose={clearError}`\n\n---\n\n### **8. File Structure & Locations**\n\n| Component | File Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| Error Context | `/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` | Error state management + parsing |\n| Page Component | `/pages/CoinflipPage.tsx` | Error toast rendering |\n| Toast Component | `/packages/ui/src/components/Toast.tsx` | Reusable toast UI |\n| CSS Styles | `/apps/platform/src/index.css` | Toast & error-toast styling |\n\n---\n\n### **Summary**\n\nThe coinflip UI uses a **context-based error system** with:\n- **Central error state** in CoinflipContext\n- **Smart error parsing** that converts Solana/Anchor errors to user-friendly messages\n- **Portal-based toast rendering** (fixed at bottom center)\n- **Visual distinction** with red border + gold-tinted background for errors\n- **User control** to dismiss via X button\n- **Specific messages** for insufficient balance, locked matches, ownership conflicts, etc.\n\nThe system gracefully handles all three error scenarios you asked about with specific, helpful error messages."}],"totalDurationMs":78060,"totalTokens":71735,"totalToolUseCount":28,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":260,"cache_read_input_tokens":68292,"output_tokens":3183,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":260,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RzQ3FSp7LoBjjsKPzQieym","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the infrastructure. Let me implement the error-flow tests. Based on the exploration:\n\n1. **Insufficient balance**: Create a match when wallet has very little SOL. The error message should be \"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL to complete this transaction.\"\n\n2. **Join locked match**: This would mean trying to join a match that's already in the locked/resolved phase. The error message would be \"This match is no longer available.\"\n\n3. **Loser claim attempt**: After a match resolves, the loser tries to claim. The error would surface through the UI.\n\nLet me think about how to implement each scenario:\n\n\nFor the insufficient balance test, I need a player with just enough SOL for gas fees but not enough for the Iron tier entry fee of 5,000,000 lamports. The simplest approach is to create a new keypair with a minimal airdrop rather than trying to work around the existing fixture players. For the insufficient balance test, I'll fund player A with just enough SOL to cover gas fees but not the entry cost for the iron tier match, then verify the error gets thrown when trying to create a match.\n\nFor the locked match scenario, I need player A to create a match first, then have player B join to lock it, so when a third player attempts to join afterward, they hit the locked state error. I'm realizing the core issue: with our two-player setup and the VRF resolving immediately after creation, I need to think through the actual sequence. The match flows create → join → VRF resolve, so for a \"locked match\" test I could have Player A create and Player B join (locking it), then attempt a third join—but we only have two players in the fixture. Alternatively, I could test joining a match that's already been resolved by the VRF, which would also be in a locked state. that same locked match\n\nSince we only have two players in the fixture, this is hard to do via UI alone. But maybe we can:\n- Create the match with Player A\n- Join with Player B (match becomes locked/resolved)  \n- Then... we need a third party.\n\nOR... we can simulate it differently:\n- Player A creates a match\n- Before Player B joins, lock the match programmatically (e.g., by writing to the account)\n\nActually, let me re-read the FR:\n> - [ ] Joining an already-locked match shows an error message\n\nThe key test is: the UI shows an error when you try to join a match that's locked. How would this happen in practice?\n\nIn the real app:\n1. Match appears in lobby\n2. Before you click join, someone else joins it\n3. You click join, it fails because the match is now locked\n\nWith our fixture, the simplest approach is to have Player A create a match, then use Solana directly to lock it before Player B attempts to join through the UI, so we can properly test the error handling. join a match, leaving it in locked state\n- Then have Player B try to join via the UI\n\nBut our page-object `joinMatch` clicks the join button in the lobby. If the match is already locked, it might not show up in the lobby at all...\n\nLet me think about this differently. The tests are about error handling in the UI. The spec says three scenarios:\n1. Insufficient balance → error message\n2. Join locked match → error message\n3. Loser claim → error message\n\nFor #2, maybe the practical test is:\n- Two players race to join the same match\n- Or: Player A creates a match, it appears in B's lobby, then we programmatically lock it (via raw transaction), THEN Player B clicks join\n\nFor the programmatic approach, I'd need to send a joinMatch transaction directly via the RPC, then have B try through the UI.\n\nActually, looking at the lifecycle test more carefully—Player A creates, Player B joins, VRF resolves, then we determine winner/loser. For the \"join locked match\" error, I can't really show the match in the lobby again after it's locked. That doesn't make sense from a UX standpoint.\n\nLet me focus on what the spec actually needs tested. The insufficient balance case is straightforward—fund minimally and try to create. For the loser claim, that happens after resolution. For the locked match scenario, I could engineer a race where a programmatic transaction locks the match right after the lobby renders it but before the user clicks join. I need to test the locked state properly—if Player A creates a match and a third keypair joins via direct RPC before Player B can, the match becomes locked and Player B's join attempt should fail. The tricky part is that a locked match might not even appear in the lobby, so I need to verify what error message Player B actually gets when trying to join a match that's already been claimed. is visible to Player B, we programmatically send a join transaction from a third wallet while the card is still showing, then Player B clicks join on the stale card and should get an error that the match is no longer available. I'll need to create a third keypair for this scenario.\n\nFor the loser claim test, after Player A wins and Player B loses, Player B should see a loss state, but the UI probably shows \"Settle & Return\" instead of a claim button for losers. The spec mentions that claiming as the loser should show an error, so I need to figure out if the UI even allows that action or if it's blocked at the interface level. So the key distinction is that `claimPayout()` would fail on-chain if the loser tries to call it directly, since the instruction verifies the winner. The UI probably handles this by showing \"Settle & Return\" to the loser instead, which likely calls a different function that closes the match and returns the rent without any payout. The test needs to verify that the loser can't successfully claim even if they attempt to invoke the claim instruction directly. I'm realizing the UI probably prevents the loser from even seeing a claim button—they'd get \"Settle & Return\" instead—so there's no error to show in the normal flow. To test the actual error case, I'd need to either call the claim function directly via `page.evaluate` or intercept the RPC call. Let me just dive into the CoinflipContext code to understand how claim and settle actually work, then I can figure out the right testing approach.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7518,"cache_read_input_tokens":46830,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7518},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9011bcd3-c1e3-4ba2-996b-dc56e2b15fd6","uuid":"3c1ca333-2255-4ae0-9c1e-f306e1dc85c9"}
