{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RuzLuzBqWAndnxMBo16Cbp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { useState, useEffect } from \"react\";\n     2→import type { UIMatch } from \"../types\";\n     3→import type { VerificationResult } from \"../utils/verification\";\n     4→import { CoinAnimation } from \"./CoinAnimation\";\n     5→import { getOppositeSide } from \"../utils/helpers\";\n     6→import { PlayerAvatarCompact } from \"../../player-profile\";\n     7→\n     8→const LOCK_TIMEOUT_MS = 120_000; // 2 minutes\n     9→\n    10→interface ActiveMatchViewProps {\n    11→  match: UIMatch;\n    12→  currentUserAddress: string;\n    13→  onCancel?: () => void;\n    14→  onTimeoutCancel?: () => void;\n    15→  onClaim?: () => void;\n    16→  onClearMatch?: () => void;\n    17→  onRematch?: () => void;\n    18→  cancelling?: boolean;\n    19→  claiming?: boolean;\n    20→  rematching?: boolean;\n    21→  // Verification\n    22→  claimTxSignature?: string | null;\n    23→  verificationResult?: VerificationResult | null;\n    24→  verifying?: boolean;\n    25→  onVerify?: () => void;\n    26→}\n    27→\n    28→export function ActiveMatchView({\n    29→  match,\n    30→  currentUserAddress,\n    31→  onCancel,\n    32→  onTimeoutCancel,\n    33→  onClaim,\n    34→  onClearMatch,\n    35→  onRematch,\n    36→  cancelling,\n    37→  claiming,\n    38→  rematching,\n    39→  claimTxSignature,\n    40→  verificationResult,\n    41→  verifying,\n    42→  onVerify,\n    43→}: ActiveMatchViewProps) {\n    44→  const isPlayer1 = match.player1 === currentUserAddress;\n    45→  const isWinner = match.winner === currentUserAddress;\n    46→\n    47→  const yourSide = isPlayer1 ? match.player1Side : match.player2Side;\n    48→  const opponentSide = yourSide ? getOppositeSide(yourSide) : null;\n    49→  const opponent = isPlayer1 ? match.player2 : match.player1;\n    50→\n    51→  // Track whether lock timeout has elapsed (for timeout cancel button)\n    52→  const [lockTimedOut, setLockTimedOut] = useState(false);\n    53→  const [cancellingTimeout, setCancellingTimeout] = useState(false);\n    54→\n    55→  useEffect(() => {\n    56→    if (match.phase !== \"ready\" || !match.lockedAt) {\n    57→      // For legacy matches with no lockedAt, show cancel immediately\n    58→      setLockTimedOut(match.phase === \"ready\");\n    59→      return;\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    const remaining = match.lockedAt + LOCK_TIMEOUT_MS - Date.now();\n    63→    if (remaining <= 0) {\n    64→      setLockTimedOut(true);\n    65→      return;\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    setLockTimedOut(false);\n    69→    const timer = setTimeout(() => setLockTimedOut(true), remaining);\n    70→    return () => clearTimeout(timer);\n    71→  }, [match.phase, match.lockedAt]);\n    72→\n    73→  // Countdown timer\n    74→  const [countdown, setCountdown] = useState(3);\n    75→\n    76→  useEffect(() => {\n    77→    if (match.phase === \"countdown\" && match.countdownStartedAt) {\n    78→      // Always start at 3\n    79→      setCountdown(3);\n    80→\n    81→      const updateCountdown = () => {\n    82→        const elapsed = Date.now() - match.countdownStartedAt!;\n    83→        // Each number shows for exactly 1 second:\n    84→        // 0-999ms: show 3\n    85→        // 1000-1999ms: show 2\n    86→        // 2000-2999ms: show 1\n    87→        if (elapsed < 1000) {\n    88→          setCountdown(3);\n    89→        } else if (elapsed < 2000) {\n    90→          setCountdown(2);\n    91→        } else {\n    92→          setCountdown(1);\n    93→        }\n    94→      };\n    95→\n    96→      const interval = setInterval(updateCountdown, 50);\n    97→      return () => {\n    98→        clearInterval(interval);\n    99→        // Reset for next countdown\n   100→        setCountdown(3);\n   101→      };\n   102→    }\n   103→  }, [match.phase, match.countdownStartedAt]);\n   104→\n   105→  return (\n   106→    <div className=\"coinflip-active-match\">\n   107→      {/* Waiting for opponent */}\n   108→      {match.phase === \"created\" && (\n   109→        <div className=\"coinflip-active-match__waiting\">\n   110→          <h3 className=\"coinflip-active-match__title\">Waiting for Opponent</h3>\n   111→          <div className=\"coinflip-active-match__info\">\n   112→            <p>\n   113→              Your side: <strong className={`side-${match.player1Side}`}>\n   114→                {match.player1Side.toUpperCase()}\n   115→              </strong>\n   116→            </p>\n   117→            <p>Entry: <strong>{\"$\"}{match.entryAmount}</strong></p>\n   118→          </div>\n   119→          <div className=\"coinflip-waiting__spinner\" />\n   120→          <p className=\"coinflip-active-match__hint\">\n   121→            Someone will join soon...\n   122→          </p>\n   123→          {onCancel && (\n   124→            <button\n   125→              type=\"button\"\n   126→              className=\"coinflip-action-btn coinflip-action-btn--secondary\"\n   127→              onClick={onCancel}\n   128→              disabled={cancelling}\n   129→            >\n   130→              {cancelling ? \"Cancelling...\" : \"Cancel Match\"}\n   131→            </button>\n   132→          )}\n   133→        </div>\n   134→      )}\n   135→\n   136→      {/* Ready / Countdown */}\n   137→      {(match.phase === \"ready\" || match.phase === \"countdown\") && (\n   138→        <div className=\"coinflip-active-match__playing\">\n   139→          <h3 className=\"coinflip-active-match__title\">\n   140→            {match.phase === \"ready\" && \"Game Ready!\"}\n   141→            {match.phase === \"countdown\" && (\n   142→              <span className=\"coinflip-countdown-inline\">\n   143→                Flipping in... <span className=\"coinflip-countdown-inline__number\">{countdown}</span>\n   144→              </span>\n   145→            )}\n   146→          </h3>\n   147→\n   148→          <div className=\"coinflip-active-match__players\">\n   149→            <div className=\"coinflip-player coinflip-player--you\">\n   150→              <span className=\"coinflip-player__label\">\n   151→                <PlayerAvatarCompact address={currentUserAddress} />\n   152→              </span>\n   153→              <span className={`coinflip-player__side side-${yourSide}`}>\n   154→                {yourSide?.toUpperCase()}\n   155→              </span>\n   156→            </div>\n   157→\n   158→            <span className=\"coinflip-active-match__vs\">VS</span>\n   159→\n   160→            <div className=\"coinflip-player coinflip-player--opponent\">\n   161→              <span className=\"coinflip-player__label\">\n   162→                {opponent ? <PlayerAvatarCompact address={opponent} /> : \"...\"}\n   163→              </span>\n   164→              <span className={`coinflip-player__side side-${opponentSide}`}>\n   165→                {opponentSide?.toUpperCase()}\n   166→              </span>\n   167→            </div>\n   168→          </div>\n   169→\n   170→          {/* Static coin for ready/countdown phases */}\n   171→          <CoinAnimation\n   172→            isFlipping={false}\n   173→            result={null}\n   174→            initialSide={yourSide ?? \"heads\"}\n   175→            size=\"lg\"\n   176→          />\n   177→\n   178→          {/* Timeout cancel — shown when VRF hasn't resolved within 2 min */}\n   179→          {match.phase === \"ready\" && lockTimedOut && onTimeoutCancel && (\n   180→            <div className=\"coinflip-active-match__timeout\">\n   181→              <p className=\"coinflip-active-match__hint\">\n   182→                Resolution timed out.\n   183→              </p>\n   184→              <button\n   185→                type=\"button\"\n   186→                className=\"coinflip-action-btn coinflip-action-btn--secondary\"\n   187→                onClick={async () => {\n   188→                  setCancellingTimeout(true);\n   189→                  try { await onTimeoutCancel(); } finally { setCancellingTimeout(false); }\n   190→                }}\n   191→                disabled={cancellingTimeout}\n   192→              >\n   193→                {cancellingTimeout ? \"Cancelling...\" : \"Cancel & Refund\"}\n   194→              </button>\n   195→            </div>\n   196→          )}\n   197→\n   198→        </div>\n   199→      )}\n   200→\n   201→      {/* Flipping / Complete - same container so coin persists through transition */}\n   202→      {(match.phase === \"flipping\" || match.phase === \"complete\") && (\n   203→        <div className=\"coinflip-active-match__playing\">\n   204→          <h3 className={`coinflip-active-match__title ${\n   205→            match.phase === \"complete\" ? (isWinner ? \"coinflip-active-match__title--won\" : \"coinflip-active-match__title--lost\") : \"\"\n   206→          }`}>\n   207→            {match.phase === \"flipping\" && \"Flipping!\"}\n   208→            {match.phase === \"complete\" && isWinner && \"You Won!\"}\n   209→            {match.phase === \"complete\" && !isWinner && (\n   210→              <span className=\"coinflip-lose-title\">\n   211→                You Lost{\" \"}\n   212→                <span className=\"coinflip-lose-title__heart\">💔</span>\n   213→                <span className=\"coinflip-lose-title__shards\">\n   214→                  {[...Array(5)].map((_, i) => (\n   215→                    <span key={i} className=\"coinflip-lose-title__shard\" style={{ '--shard-index': i } as React.CSSProperties}>◆</span>\n   216→                  ))}\n   217→                </span>\n   218→              </span>\n   219→            )}\n   220→          </h3>\n   221→\n   222→          {/* Players info during flipping */}\n   223→          {match.phase === \"flipping\" && (\n   224→            <div className=\"coinflip-active-match__players\">\n   225→              <div className=\"coinflip-player coinflip-player--you\">\n   226→                <span className=\"coinflip-player__label\">\n   227→                  <PlayerAvatarCompact address={currentUserAddress} />\n   228→                </span>\n   229→                <span className={`coinflip-player__side side-${yourSide}`}>\n   230→                  {yourSide?.toUpperCase()}\n   231→                </span>\n   232→              </div>\n   233→\n   234→              <span className=\"coinflip-active-match__vs\">VS</span>\n   235→\n   236→              <div className=\"coinflip-player coinflip-player--opponent\">\n   237→                <span className=\"coinflip-player__label\">\n   238→                  {opponent ? <PlayerAvatarCompact address={opponent} /> : \"...\"}\n   239→                </span>\n   240→                <span className={`coinflip-player__side side-${opponentSide}`}>\n   241→                  {opponentSide?.toUpperCase()}\n   242→                </span>\n   243→              </div>\n   244→            </div>\n   245→          )}\n   246→\n   247→          {/* Single coin that persists through flipping → complete */}\n   248→          <CoinAnimation\n   249→            isFlipping={match.phase === \"flipping\"}\n   250→            result={match.result}\n   251→            initialSide={yourSide ?? \"heads\"}\n   252→            size=\"lg\"\n   253→          />\n   254→\n   255→          {/* Result info during complete */}\n   256→          {match.phase === \"complete\" && (\n   257→            <>\n   258→              {/* Win Animation - Arcade star burst */}\n   259→              {isWinner && (\n   260→                <div className=\"coinflip-win-animation\">\n   261→                  <div className=\"coinflip-win-animation__stars\">\n   262→                    {[...Array(8)].map((_, i) => (\n   263→                      <span key={i} className=\"coinflip-win-animation__star\" style={{ '--star-index': i } as React.CSSProperties}>★</span>\n   264→                    ))}\n   265→                  </div>\n   266→                  <div className=\"coinflip-win-animation__coins\">\n   267→                    {[...Array(6)].map((_, i) => (\n   268→                      <span key={i} className=\"coinflip-win-animation__coin\" style={{ '--coin-index': i } as React.CSSProperties}>●</span>\n   269→                    ))}\n   270→                  </div>\n   271→                </div>\n   272→              )}\n   273→\n   274→              <div\n   275→                className={`coinflip-result ${\n   276→                  isWinner ? \"coinflip-result--won\" : \"coinflip-result--lost\"\n   277→                }`}\n   278→              >\n   279→                <p className=\"coinflip-result__outcome\">\n   280→                  Result: <strong\n   281→                    style={{\n   282→                      color: match.result === \"heads\" ? \"#45b058\" : \"#e09030\",\n   283→                      textShadow: `0 0 6px ${match.result === \"heads\" ? \"#45b058\" : \"#e09030\"}`\n   284→                    }}\n   285→                  >{match.result?.toUpperCase()}</strong>\n   286→                </p>\n   287→                {isWinner && (\n   288→                  <p className=\"coinflip-result__payout\">\n   289→                    Payout: <strong>{\"$\"}{match.payoutAmount.toFixed(4)}</strong>\n   290→                  </p>\n   291→                )}\n   292→              </div>\n   293→\n   294→              {/* Action buttons */}\n   295→              <div className=\"coinflip-active-match__actions\">\n   296→                {!match.claimed && onClaim && (\n   297→                  <button\n   298→                    type=\"button\"\n   299→                    className=\"coinflip-action-btn\"\n   300→                    onClick={onClaim}\n   301→                    disabled={claiming}\n   302→                  >\n   303→                    {claiming\n   304→                      ? \"Settling...\"\n   305→                      : isWinner\n   306→                        ? \"Claim Payout\"\n   307→                        : \"Settle & Return to Lobby\"}\n   308→                  </button>\n   309→                )}\n   310→                {match.claimed && (\n   311→                  <div className=\"coinflip-active-match__post-claim\">\n   312→                    {onVerify && claimTxSignature && (\n   313→                      <button\n   314→                        type=\"button\"\n   315→                        className=\"coinflip-action-btn\"\n   316→                        onClick={onVerify}\n   317→                        disabled={verifying || !!verificationResult}\n   318→                      >\n   319→                        {verifying ? \"Verifying...\" : verificationResult ? \"Verified\" : \"Verify Fairness\"}\n   320→                      </button>\n   321→                    )}\n   322→                    {onRematch && (\n   323→                      <button\n   324→                        type=\"button\"\n   325→                        className=\"coinflip-action-btn\"\n   326→                        onClick={onRematch}\n   327→                        disabled={rematching}\n   328→                      >\n   329→                        {rematching ? \"Creating...\" : \"Play Again\"}\n   330→                      </button>\n   331→                    )}\n   332→                    {onClearMatch && (\n   333→                      <button\n   334→                        type=\"button\"\n   335→                        className=\"coinflip-action-btn coinflip-action-btn--secondary\"\n   336→                        onClick={onClearMatch}\n   337→                      >\n   338→                        Back to Lobby\n   339→                      </button>\n   340→                    )}\n   341→                  </div>\n   342→                )}\n   343→              </div>\n   344→\n   345→              {/* Verification panel — shown after verifyMatch completes */}\n   346→              {verificationResult && (\n   347→                <div className=\"coinflip-verification\">\n   348→                  <h4 className=\"coinflip-verification__title\">\n   349→                    Fairness Verification\n   350→                  </h4>\n   351→                  <div className={`coinflip-verification__badge ${verificationResult.verified ? \"coinflip-verification__badge--verified\" : \"coinflip-verification__badge--failed\"}`}>\n   352→                    {verificationResult.verified ? \"Verified\" : \"Failed\"}\n   353→                  </div>\n   354→                  <div className=\"coinflip-verification__rows\">\n   355→                    <div className=\"coinflip-verification__row\">\n   356→                      <span>Claim TX</span>\n   357→                      <span className=\"coinflip-verification__hash\" title={claimTxSignature ?? \"\"}>\n   358→                        {claimTxSignature ? `${claimTxSignature.slice(0, 8)}...${claimTxSignature.slice(-8)}` : \"—\"}\n   359→                      </span>\n   360→                    </div>\n   361→                    <div className=\"coinflip-verification__row\">\n   362→                      <span>Randomness</span>\n   363→                      <span className=\"coinflip-verification__hash\" title={verificationResult.randomnessHex}>\n   364→                        {verificationResult.randomnessHex.slice(0, 16)}...\n   365→                      </span>\n   366→                    </div>\n   367→                    <div className=\"coinflip-verification__row\">\n   368→                      <span>Derived Result</span>\n   369→                      <span className={`side-${verificationResult.derivedResult}`}>\n   370→                        {verificationResult.derivedResult.toUpperCase()}\n   371→                      </span>\n   372→                    </div>\n   373→                    <div className=\"coinflip-verification__row\">\n   374→                      <span>Winner</span>\n   375→                      <span className=\"coinflip-verification__hash\" title={verificationResult.winner}>\n   376→                        {verificationResult.winner.slice(0, 4)}...{verificationResult.winner.slice(-4)}\n   377→                      </span>\n   378→                    </div>\n   379→                    <div className=\"coinflip-verification__row\">\n   380→                      <span>VRF Fulfilled</span>\n   381→                      <span className={verificationResult.vrfFulfilled ? \"coinflip-verification__check\" : \"coinflip-verification__cross\"}>\n   382→                        {verificationResult.vrfFulfilled ? \"Yes\" : \"No\"}\n   383→                      </span>\n   384→                    </div>\n   385→                  </div>\n   386→                  <a href=\"/fairness\" className=\"coinflip-verification__link\">\n   387→                    Full Verification Page\n   388→                  </a>\n   389→                </div>\n   390→              )}\n   391→\n   392→            </>\n   393→          )}\n   394→        </div>\n   395→      )}\n   396→    </div>\n   397→  );\n   398→}\n   399→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01X9FiBdT9B8AHWyxFDKe8xG","session_id":"9011bcd3-c1e3-4ba2-996b-dc56e2b15fd6","uuid":"bf5b964b-a141-4a29-96ba-c471d7f7fc91"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X9FiBdT9B8AHWyxFDKe8xG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the pieces. Let me compile a comprehensive report on the claim/settle flow.\n\n## Summary: Coinflip Claim/Settle Flow for Winners vs Losers\n\nBased on my analysis of the frontend context, pages, chain utilities, and on-chain program code, here's the exact behavior:\n\n### **1. UI Button Display (Frontend Level)**\n\nIn **`CoinflipPage.tsx` (lines 300-312)**, the button shown depends on the player's win status:\n\n```tsx\n{activeMatch.phase === \"complete\" && !activeMatch.claimed && (\n  <button\n    type=\"button\"\n    className=\"coinflip-action-btn\"\n    onClick={claimPayout}\n    disabled={claiming}\n  >\n    {claiming\n      ? \"Settling...\"\n      : activeMatch.winner === address\n        ? \"Claim Payout\"          // ← Winner sees this\n        : \"Settle & Return\"}       // ← Loser sees this\n  </button>\n)}\n```\n\n**Same button for both** — The UI does NOT prevent losers from clicking. Both winner and loser see a clickable button (unless `claiming` is true). The button text changes, but the action (`claimPayout`) is identical for both.\n\nIn **`ActiveMatchView.tsx` (lines 296-308)**, the same logic applies when showing the claim button:\n\n```tsx\n{!match.claimed && onClaim && (\n  <button\n    type=\"button\"\n    className=\"coinflip-action-btn\"\n    onClick={onClaim}\n    disabled={claiming}\n  >\n    {claiming\n      ? \"Settling...\"\n      : isWinner\n        ? \"Claim Payout\"\n        : \"Settle & Return to Lobby\"}\n  </button>\n)}\n```\n\n### **2. Transaction Building**\n\nIn **`chain.ts` (lines 427-480)**, there is **only ONE function**: `buildClaimPayoutTx`. No separate `buildSettleTx`:\n\n```typescript\nexport async function buildClaimPayoutTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  caller: PublicKey,      // Either player (winner or loser)\n  matchCreator: PublicKey,\n  opponent: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction>\n```\n\nThe same transaction builder is called for both winner and loser. The builder does NOT check if the caller is the winner—that check happens **on-chain**.\n\n### **3. Context API**\n\nIn **`CoinflipContext.tsx` (lines 433-470)**, there is only **ONE function**: `claimPayout`. No separate `settleLosing` function:\n\n```typescript\nconst claimPayout = useCallback(async () => {\n  // ...\n  const transaction = await buildClaimPayoutTx(\n    connection,\n    publicKey,   // caller (either player — winner derived on-chain)\n    matchCreator,\n    opponent\n  );\n  const signature = await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n  // ...\n}, [connected, publicKey, activeMatch, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]);\n```\n\nThe comment explicitly says: **\"winner derived on-chain from VRF\"** — implying the on-chain program figures out the winner, not the frontend.\n\n### **4. On-Chain Enforcement (Solana Program)**\n\nIn **`claim_payout.rs` (lines 68-179)**, the program DOES enforce that the transaction can be called by either player, but the payout logic determines winner based on VRF:\n\n**Key enforcements (lines 71-101):**\n```rust\n// (1) Must be in LOCKED phase and not already claimed\nrequire!(\n    coinflip_match.phase == RoundPhase::Locked,\n    CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n);\nrequire!(!coinflip_match.claimed, CoinflipError::AlreadyClaimed);\n\n// Caller must be either creator or opponent\nlet caller = ctx.accounts.caller.key();\nrequire!(\n    caller == coinflip_match.creator || caller == coinflip_match.opponent,\n    CoinflipError::UnauthorizedCaller\n);\n```\n\n**Winner derivation (lines 103-112):**\n```rust\n// (2) Read Orao randomness — rejects if not fulfilled\nlet randomness = read_orao_randomness(&ctx.accounts.randomness_account)?;\n\n// (3) Derive winner from randomness\nlet result = from_randomness(randomness[0]);\nlet winner = if result == coinflip_match.creator_side {\n    coinflip_match.creator\n} else {\n    coinflip_match.opponent\n};\n```\n\n**Payout logic (lines 114-126):**\n```rust\nlet pool = coinflip_match.entry_amount.checked_mul(2).unwrap();\nlet (fee, payout) = calculate_net_payout(pool);\n\n// Transfer payout to winner + fee to treasury\nlet winner_account = if winner == coinflip_match.creator {\n    ctx.accounts.creator.to_account_info()\n} else {\n    ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info()\n};\ntransfer_lamports_from_pda(&match_info, &winner_account, payout)?;\ntransfer_lamports_from_pda(&match_info, &ctx.accounts.treasury, fee)?;\n```\n\n### **5. What Happens When Loser Tries to Claim?**\n\n1. **Frontend**: Button is shown to both winner and loser. Loser can click it.\n2. **Transaction**: Same `buildClaimPayoutTx` is used; both players pass the same signed transaction.\n3. **On-chain**:\n   - The program accepts the loser as the caller (passes `UnauthorizedCaller` check).\n   - The program reads the VRF randomness and derives the **true winner**.\n   - The program **transfers the payout to the winner** (not the caller/loser).\n   - The program **charges the loser's entry amount** against the pool (refund = 0 for loser).\n   - The program records `winner = true_winner_pubkey` and `claimed = true`.\n\n**Result**: The loser gets **no payout** (their entire entry amount goes to winner + treasury fees). The transaction succeeds, but the loser receives 0 lamports. They see \"Settle & Return\" button, click it, and the transaction confirms successfully—but they get nothing.\n\n### **6. Button Visibility in Lobby**\n\nIn **`CoinflipPage.tsx` (lines 375-382)**, claimable matches show action labels based on winner status:\n\n```tsx\nlet actionLabel: string;\nif (match.phase === \"complete\") {\n  actionLabel = match.winner === address ? \"Claim\" : \"Settle\";\n} else if (match.phase === \"created\" && isCreator) {\n  actionLabel = \"Cancel\";\n} else {\n  actionLabel = \"View\";\n}\n```\n\nBoth winner and loser see a clickable card in \"Your Matches\" with either \"Claim\" or \"Settle\" button.\n\n---\n\n## Answer to Your Core Question\n\n**\"When the loser tries to claim, does the UI prevent it (no button shown) or does it attempt the tx and show an error?\"**\n\n**The UI does NOT prevent it.** The loser sees the \"Settle & Return\" button alongside the winner's \"Claim Payout\" button. If the loser clicks it:\n\n1. The same transaction is built and signed.\n2. It is sent on-chain and executes successfully.\n3. The on-chain program reads the VRF result, determines the true winner, and transfers the payout to the **winner** (not the loser).\n4. The loser receives **0 lamports** but the transaction commits (no error thrown).\n5. The frontend shows the match as `claimed: true` and allows the loser to verify fairness or go back to lobby.\n\n**No UI error message is shown**—the settlement happens silently at the on-chain level."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a63246cffbc5dea20 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63947\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 43303</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9011bcd3-c1e3-4ba2-996b-dc56e2b15fd6","uuid":"b39b29a8-55fa-40d3-8c36-96d62bc93336","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand specifically how the coinflip UI handles the claim/settle flow for winners vs losers. Look at:\n\n1. `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` - specifically the `claimPayout` and any `settle` functions. What does the loser see/do? Is there a separate settle function? What happens when the loser tries to claim?\n\n2. `apps/platform/src/pages/CoinflipPage.tsx` - What buttons are shown to the winner vs loser? Is \"Claim Payout\" shown to the loser? Is there a \"Settle & Return\" button? What action does each button trigger?\n\n3. `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` - What transaction builders exist? Is there a `buildClaimPayoutTx` and a separate `buildSettleTx`? Or just one function for both?\n\n4. The coinflip program IDL or source: `solana/programs/coinflip/src/` - What instructions exist for claim? Is there a separate settle instruction? What validations exist (e.g., only winner can claim)?\n\nFocus specifically on: When the loser tries to claim, does the UI prevent it (no button shown) or does it attempt the tx and show an error? I need the exact behavior.\n\nRoot path: /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/","agentId":"a63246cffbc5dea20","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the pieces. Let me compile a comprehensive report on the claim/settle flow.\n\n## Summary: Coinflip Claim/Settle Flow for Winners vs Losers\n\nBased on my analysis of the frontend context, pages, chain utilities, and on-chain program code, here's the exact behavior:\n\n### **1. UI Button Display (Frontend Level)**\n\nIn **`CoinflipPage.tsx` (lines 300-312)**, the button shown depends on the player's win status:\n\n```tsx\n{activeMatch.phase === \"complete\" && !activeMatch.claimed && (\n  <button\n    type=\"button\"\n    className=\"coinflip-action-btn\"\n    onClick={claimPayout}\n    disabled={claiming}\n  >\n    {claiming\n      ? \"Settling...\"\n      : activeMatch.winner === address\n        ? \"Claim Payout\"          // ← Winner sees this\n        : \"Settle & Return\"}       // ← Loser sees this\n  </button>\n)}\n```\n\n**Same button for both** — The UI does NOT prevent losers from clicking. Both winner and loser see a clickable button (unless `claiming` is true). The button text changes, but the action (`claimPayout`) is identical for both.\n\nIn **`ActiveMatchView.tsx` (lines 296-308)**, the same logic applies when showing the claim button:\n\n```tsx\n{!match.claimed && onClaim && (\n  <button\n    type=\"button\"\n    className=\"coinflip-action-btn\"\n    onClick={onClaim}\n    disabled={claiming}\n  >\n    {claiming\n      ? \"Settling...\"\n      : isWinner\n        ? \"Claim Payout\"\n        : \"Settle & Return to Lobby\"}\n  </button>\n)}\n```\n\n### **2. Transaction Building**\n\nIn **`chain.ts` (lines 427-480)**, there is **only ONE function**: `buildClaimPayoutTx`. No separate `buildSettleTx`:\n\n```typescript\nexport async function buildClaimPayoutTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  caller: PublicKey,      // Either player (winner or loser)\n  matchCreator: PublicKey,\n  opponent: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction>\n```\n\nThe same transaction builder is called for both winner and loser. The builder does NOT check if the caller is the winner—that check happens **on-chain**.\n\n### **3. Context API**\n\nIn **`CoinflipContext.tsx` (lines 433-470)**, there is only **ONE function**: `claimPayout`. No separate `settleLosing` function:\n\n```typescript\nconst claimPayout = useCallback(async () => {\n  // ...\n  const transaction = await buildClaimPayoutTx(\n    connection,\n    publicKey,   // caller (either player — winner derived on-chain)\n    matchCreator,\n    opponent\n  );\n  const signature = await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n  // ...\n}, [connected, publicKey, activeMatch, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]);\n```\n\nThe comment explicitly says: **\"winner derived on-chain from VRF\"** — implying the on-chain program figures out the winner, not the frontend.\n\n### **4. On-Chain Enforcement (Solana Program)**\n\nIn **`claim_payout.rs` (lines 68-179)**, the program DOES enforce that the transaction can be called by either player, but the payout logic determines winner based on VRF:\n\n**Key enforcements (lines 71-101):**\n```rust\n// (1) Must be in LOCKED phase and not already claimed\nrequire!(\n    coinflip_match.phase == RoundPhase::Locked,\n    CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n);\nrequire!(!coinflip_match.claimed, CoinflipError::AlreadyClaimed);\n\n// Caller must be either creator or opponent\nlet caller = ctx.accounts.caller.key();\nrequire!(\n    caller == coinflip_match.creator || caller == coinflip_match.opponent,\n    CoinflipError::UnauthorizedCaller\n);\n```\n\n**Winner derivation (lines 103-112):**\n```rust\n// (2) Read Orao randomness — rejects if not fulfilled\nlet randomness = read_orao_randomness(&ctx.accounts.randomness_account)?;\n\n// (3) Derive winner from randomness\nlet result = from_randomness(randomness[0]);\nlet winner = if result == coinflip_match.creator_side {\n    coinflip_match.creator\n} else {\n    coinflip_match.opponent\n};\n```\n\n**Payout logic (lines 114-126):**\n```rust\nlet pool = coinflip_match.entry_amount.checked_mul(2).unwrap();\nlet (fee, payout) = calculate_net_payout(pool);\n\n// Transfer payout to winner + fee to treasury\nlet winner_account = if winner == coinflip_match.creator {\n    ctx.accounts.creator.to_account_info()\n} else {\n    ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info()\n};\ntransfer_lamports_from_pda(&match_info, &winner_account, payout)?;\ntransfer_lamports_from_pda(&match_info, &ctx.accounts.treasury, fee)?;\n```\n\n### **5. What Happens When Loser Tries to Claim?**\n\n1. **Frontend**: Button is shown to both winner and loser. Loser can click it.\n2. **Transaction**: Same `buildClaimPayoutTx` is used; both players pass the same signed transaction.\n3. **On-chain**:\n   - The program accepts the loser as the caller (passes `UnauthorizedCaller` check).\n   - The program reads the VRF randomness and derives the **true winner**.\n   - The program **transfers the payout to the winner** (not the caller/loser).\n   - The program **charges the loser's entry amount** against the pool (refund = 0 for loser).\n   - The program records `winner = true_winner_pubkey` and `claimed = true`.\n\n**Result**: The loser gets **no payout** (their entire entry amount goes to winner + treasury fees). The transaction succeeds, but the loser receives 0 lamports. They see \"Settle & Return\" button, click it, and the transaction confirms successfully—but they get nothing.\n\n### **6. Button Visibility in Lobby**\n\nIn **`CoinflipPage.tsx` (lines 375-382)**, claimable matches show action labels based on winner status:\n\n```tsx\nlet actionLabel: string;\nif (match.phase === \"complete\") {\n  actionLabel = match.winner === address ? \"Claim\" : \"Settle\";\n} else if (match.phase === \"created\" && isCreator) {\n  actionLabel = \"Cancel\";\n} else {\n  actionLabel = \"View\";\n}\n```\n\nBoth winner and loser see a clickable card in \"Your Matches\" with either \"Claim\" or \"Settle\" button.\n\n---\n\n## Answer to Your Core Question\n\n**\"When the loser tries to claim, does the UI prevent it (no button shown) or does it attempt the tx and show an error?\"**\n\n**The UI does NOT prevent it.** The loser sees the \"Settle & Return\" button alongside the winner's \"Claim Payout\" button. If the loser clicks it:\n\n1. The same transaction is built and signed.\n2. It is sent on-chain and executes successfully.\n3. The on-chain program reads the VRF result, determines the true winner, and transfers the payout to the **winner** (not the loser).\n4. The loser receives **0 lamports** but the transaction commits (no error thrown).\n5. The frontend shows the match as `claimed: true` and allows the loser to verify fairness or go back to lobby.\n\n**No UI error message is shown**—the settlement happens silently at the on-chain level."}],"totalDurationMs":43303,"totalTokens":63947,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5544,"cache_read_input_tokens":56484,"output_tokens":1914,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5544,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
